  ******  Linbox Library  ******  

 


The Linbox library provides functionalities for linear algebra.


          FUNCTIONALITIES :

 Algorithms      : Gauss, Wiedemann, Valence, BlackBox composition, transposition ...
 Interfaces      : BlackBox, Field, Random Generators.
 Wrappers        : Domain (homomorphic absolute value, classical class with *,+,/..), BlackBox (vector < sparse_vector < T > >).
 Implementations : Galois Field, Z/pZ, vector < sparse_vector< T > >.


          AVAILABILITY :
The sources of this library are available : http://www-apache.imag.fr/~jgdumas/Softwares/Linbox.tar.gz : 
Linbox.tar.gz (150K, 
Last update : Friday, March 17th 2000
However, linbox team developers should work from the Subversion repository.
).

          REQUIREMENTS :  

This library requires the GNU C++ compiler (gcc-2.95.1 or newer) or any compiler supporting
advanced template features.

